{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"aa1756d8-7408-4012-9f08-72102db504d5","content":"To switch from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform with MSTest.Sdk 3.8.0:\n\n1. **Remove** (or set to `false`) the `<UseVSTest>` property in your project file:\n   ```xml\n   <!-- Delete this line or set to false -->\n   <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n   ```\n\n2. That's it — **MSTest.Sdk 3.8.0 defaults to Microsoft.Testing.Platform** when `UseVSTest` is not set to `true`.\n\n3. **Run tests** with:\n   ```\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   or directly via the built executable (Microsoft.Testing.Platform produces a self-contained test host).\n\n**Key behavioral differences to be aware of:**\n- The test output format changes (new console logger).\n- Some VSTest-specific `.runsettings` options may not apply; check for warnings.\n- If you use `dotnet test`, it works transparently. If you rely on `vstest.console.exe` directly, switch to `dotnet test` or the native test executable.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5fa5c91c-b907-4ef1-a343-0e3c2527ccaa","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in their MSTest project. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing configuration, not a code change request in a specific repository.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of MSTest.Sdk and Microsoft.Testing.Platform.","outputTokens":342},"id":"86a05833-9772-4976-a62b-6a803eab427d","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:45:52.157Z","parentId":"279412b6-0854-4587-97ee-584452605f90"}
